+        <article class="hero-panel stack">
+          <p class="eyebrow">Teacher-owned · Troy, Alabama</p>
+          <h1>Strong reading and math foundations for 1st and 2nd graders.</h1>
+          <p>I’m TeAndrea Burnett. I teach all day in the classroom and tutor with the same care after school. Families choose my sessions when they want steady practice, clear instruction, and real progress they can see at home.</p>
+          <p>I prioritize reading and math fluency first because those skills support every subject. Sessions also include science and social studies support when needed.</p>
+          <div class="button-row">
+            <a class="btn" href="/schedule.html">Book a 1-hour session</a>
+            <a class="youtube-link" href="https://www.youtube.com/@teandreaburnett0910" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Watch Teaching Videos on YouTube ↗</a>
+          </div>
+        </article>
+        <aside class="card stack">
+          <h2>Quick facts</h2>
+          <ul>
+            <li>One-hour sessions only</li>
+            <li>$25 per student</li>
+            <li>Up to 5 students per hour slot</li>
+            <li>One session per student each day</li>
+          </ul>
+          <div class="note-box"><strong>Booking flow:</strong> submit booking → pay Cash App → confirm payment.</div>
+        </aside>
+      </section>
+
+      <section class="container stack">
+        <h2>Subjects and skills covered</h2>
+        <div class="grid grid-2">
+          <article class="card"><h3>English Language Arts</h3><p>Letter sounds, phonics patterns, sight words, blending, sentence reading, basic comprehension, sentence writing, capitalization, and punctuation.</p></article>
+          <article class="card"><h3>Math</h3><p>Addition/subtraction within 20, counting to 120, tens/ones place value, number comparisons, word problems, basic time skills, and shapes.</p></article>
+          <article class="card"><h3>Science</h3><p>Plants and animals, weather patterns, and foundational light/sound concepts.</p></article>
+          <article class="card"><h3>Social Studies</h3><p>Family/community roles, maps and directions, and national symbols.</p></article>
